    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of birch tree abundant throughout northern Europe, Iceland, northern Asia, and Greenland. It is a deciduous tree growing to over 60 feet tall (18 m), with a slender crown and a trunk, having smooth dull gray-white bark finely marked with dark horizontal lenticels. It is closely related to, and often confused with the silver birch.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
